FT  19 DEC 94 / Company News (This Week and Next): E Midlands holders hope
for more cheer - Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
East Midlands Electricity will today bring the power results season to a
close when it announces profits and dividends for the half-year to September
30. Last October the company announced it was to give back Pounds 186m to
shareholders as a special dividend, or 85p per share. It chose this route
rather than buying back shares. The interim dividend may therefore be less
generous than other regional electricity companies have been able to
provide. Nonetheless, at least 15 per cent is expected and profits are
likely to be well ahead.
</TEXT>
