<HEADLINE>
FT  19 DEC 94 / This Week: Film/Video
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIGEL ANDREWS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
What should we do to film distributors for Christmas? Is there anything
punitive enough? Possessed of the spirit of Scrooge, they are introducing
just one film in the week before Christmas - a US offering about
little-league ice hockey that is a second visit to a story which was silly
enough the first time. D2: The Mighty Ducks (the sequel) will lure no one
from their turkey, even though it is one. If you want a treat this week, you
must choose among films already on release. The Nightmare Before Christmas
remains the top ticket. Nanni Moretti's Dear Diary is still the sweetest
auteur comedy since early Woody Allen. And The Adventures Of Priscilla,
Queen Of The Desert is a high-camp charmer from Down Under.
As for last week's Princess Caraboo, (above) it is almost funny enough to be
considered. Kevin Kline steals the show as a Greek butler, though the show
is erratic. Plot: is the vagrant girl played by Phoebe Cates (Mrs Kline)
really an Indonesian princess? If not, how silly will the 19th century Brits
and aristos who adopt her feel, having feted her, festooned her in
fashionable dresses and all but fed her to the Prince Regent (John
Sessions). Witty; could be wittier; worth seeing on a rainy day.
Meanwhile, Macaulay Culkin maniacs have the boy times two. He is dull in The
Pagemaster but he is a treat - childhood idiocy made radiant - in The
Nutcracker, where he capers about in the filmed ballet wearing his Home
Alone grin, mischief-making moue and flapping eyelids.
Your VCR will probably go through industrial stress over the next seven
days, what with Brief Encounter, the complete works of James Bond - and
children playing video games of Einsteinian complexity. For thoughtful
relaxation you could try two new issues. Fellini's Roma is the maestro's
slyly beautiful mockumentary about the Eternal City. And Innocent Moves, the
tale of a boy chess prodigy, makes this sit-down game more exciting than any
sport, including ice hockey.
</TEXT>
