FT  19 DEC 94 / Holidaymakers may sue Cunard
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cunard, the shipping line owned by engineering and property conglomerate
Trafalgar House, may be sued by holidaymakers denied a Christmas cruise on
the QE2, Alan Cane writes. About 300 passengers were turned away hours
before the liner set sail for New York on Saturday because of unfinished
plumbing in about 100 of the 950 cabins. The action led to scuffles and
chaos in the departure lounge. The QE2 returned from the Blohm and Voss
shipyard in Hamburg last week where it had been undergoing a Pounds 30m
refit. Sub-contractors had been working round the clock since the return to
complete refurbishments on time but without success. Neither Cunard nor
Trafalgar House could be contacted for comment last night. Reports suggest
the shipping line had been offering disappointed holidaymakers a full
refund, a free transatlantic cruise next year and Pounds 250 cash.
