FT  19 DEC 94 / Russia signs energy charter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER WISE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Russia has overcome long-standing reservations and joined 45 other nations
in signing a European Energy Charter designed as the single most important
instrument for stimulating the integration of former eastern bloc economies
into the world market. However, the US declined to sign the treaty in Lisbon
on Saturday, mainly because it considers the charter fails to guarantee
adequate protection for investors and falls below standards already obtained
by the US in bilateral and other multilateral investment agreements. The
treaty provides free and equal access to energy markets among the
signatories.
