<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Baris chairman leaves after less than a
month
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Andrew Morton has resigned as chairman of Baris Holdings, the drylining
and fire protection systems group, after less than a month. Mr John Foley
has become chairman and chief executive.
Mr Morton's resignation, due to the 'increasing time requirements' of the
other companies of which he is chairman, came as Baris reported an interim
pre-tax loss of Pounds 1.29m compared with a profit of Pounds 143,000 last
time. Sales for the six months to September 30 were 33 per cent down at
Pounds 5.43m (Pounds 8.14m).
This half's deficit included a Pounds 1.1m exceptional item relating to
costs and write-offs as a result of withdrawal from the German market.
Losses per share came out at 20.5p (0.1p earnings).
