<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Land Securities' Pounds 76.5m sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON LONDON, Property Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Land Securities has sold its Milton Gate office block in the City of London
to AP Fonden, the Swedish national pension fund, for Pounds 76.5m.
The building is let to Price Waterhouse, the accountancy firm, on a 25-year
lease from June 1990, when the building was first occupied, with a break in
2002.
The annual rent is Pounds 6.9m, or about Pounds 44 per sq ft. This is well
above the current headline rents for top City offices of about Pounds 35 per
sq ft.
The exit yield of 8.85 per cent reflects the fact that the building is
unlikely to show rental growth for some years.
Mr Ian Henderson, a director of Land Securities, said the building had been
sold at above book value, which is based on its revaluation at March 1994.
'The disposal reflects our policy of adjusting the balance our portfolio
away from City offices,' he said.
The acquisition is AP Fonden's second large deal in the City this year. In
the summer it acquired nearby Angel Court for about Pounds 60m. The fund
also owns Four Millbank, near Westminster.
</TEXT>
